```
=IF(AND(A1<>"",B1<>""),A1+B1,"")
```

We will place this formula into cell C1 of the same sheet, save the workbook to the output directory with the same filename, call `recalculate()` to evaluate the formula, and then reload the file with `data_only=True` to verify that C1 now contains a value (or remains blank if either A1 or B1 is empty).
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import column_index_from_string
import shutil
import os

# Paths
input_path = input_spreadsheet  # e.g., /sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_52220_init.xlsx
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet"
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, os.path.basename(input_path))

# Load workbook
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path)
# Assume we work on the active sheet (or first sheet)
ws = wb.active

# Write the formula into C1
ws["C1"] = "=IF(AND(A1<>\"\",B1<>\"\"),A1+B1,\"\")"

# Save to output path
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate (LibreOffice)
recalculate(output_path)

# Verify the result
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check.active
c1_val = ws_check["C1"].value
print("C1 after recalculation:", c1_val)
```
